Still on politics, could the talk of transformation of the One Kenya alliance be premature? Well, this is the question on political minds, after the alliance co-principals Musalia Mudavadi, Kalonzo Musyoka, Moses Wetangula, and Gideon Moi, announced a commitment to a new coalition, but without timelines within which they would officially leave their current alliances. Tonight our senior political affairs reporter Murimi Mwangi, revisits timelines leading to previous coalitions, and explains why Kenyans are yet to see it all in the pre-2022 poll re-alignments.